GOGII’S PRIVACY POLICY
This Privacy Policy governs your use of Gogii’s website and/or mobile applications. By using or accessing Gogii’s website and/or mobile applications you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and expressly consent to Gogii collecting, using and disclosing the information specified herein for the uses set out herein. As used herein, “personal information” or “personally identifiable information” means information about an identifiable individual. Gogii does not merge, nor facilitate the merger, of your personally identifiable information with non-personally identifiable information.
YOU MAY WITHDRAW YOUR CONSENT AT ANY TIME BY CONTACTING GOGII THROUGH ITS WEBSITE OR AT THE ADDRESS BELOW.
1. ACCOUNTABILITY
The principles of Privacy are from the Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act, Canada (PIPEDA). The Office of the Privacy Commissioner of Canada (the “OPCC”) is responsible for administering PIPEDA and ensuring compliance. The OPCC can be contacted at http://www.priv.gc.ca/index_e.cfm
If you have any questions about Gogii’s Policy, please contact us through our website or write to us at: Gogii Games Corp. 168 Valmont Crescent Dieppe, New Brunswick E1A 1N2 If there are still any unanswered questions or concerns, If there are still any unanswered questions or concerns, please contact
privacy@gogiigames.com
2. WHAT PERSONAL DATA DOES GOGII COLLECT
2.1. WE COLLECT THE DATA YOU GRANT US ACCESS.
Data we receive if you link a third party tool with the Service (such as Facebook or Google)
Contact information (such as name and email address)
Any information you submit to our customer service team in the Game or via email
2.2 WE ALSO HAVE SOME DATA WE COLLECT AUTOMATICALLY.
Data about your account, game progress and analytics about your use of our Services (e.g. in-game play progress, levels, games played, session length)
Your IP address and device identifiers such as your Advertising ID, Device ID numbers (for more see here "Advertising IDs and Device IDs")
Data about your device, such as device name and operating system, browser type and language
General location data
Precise geo-location data (GPS, with your consent)
2.3 WE ALSO HAVE SOME DATA WE OBTAIN FROM THIRD PARTY SOURCES.
(2.3.1) Information from Facebook platform.
You may choose to connect to our Services via your Facebook account. The exact information we receive from you will depend on your social media privacy settings, but it will typically include your basic public profile information, such as:
Your username
Profile picture
Age range
Gender
Your friends playing the same Game
Typical uses include updating game progress on multiple devices you may own so that you can continue your progress using multiple devices. In addition, we may show your Facebook friends in the Game and show your public Facebook profile name and picture in Game leaderboards and in your Game profile.
(2.3.2) Third party service providers.
We may receive personal information about you from third-party sources. We may get your personal information, for example, when you installed our Game or when, prior to installation, you click on an advertisement for the Game.
(2.3.3) Advertising partners.
From time to time, we may also receive personal information about you from other third-party sources. For example, if you clicked on an advertisement directing you to one of our Services (such as an ad for one of our Games in another publishers’ game), we will be provided with information about which ad network and advertising campaign the install originated from (See also "Advertising" below).
3. WHY WE COLLECT YOUR DATA
Analytics Providers provide Gogii with ad tracking and help us collect, aggregate and prepare certain information about how you use our services as well as how our services are performing.
3.1 TO MAKE THE SERVICE WORK.
Create accounts and allow you to play our games and use our Service
Operate the Service
Verify and confirm payments
Provide and deliver products and services you request
To provide you with the correct versions of our games and/or applications (e.g. knowing which language to make our games available to you in)
Send you Service-related communications
3.2 TO MAKE THE SERVICE MORE SUITABLE FOR OUR PLAYERS
To provide a great Service to our players, we have a legitimate interest to collect and process necessary data to
Update and develop player profiles
Develop and improve the Service and player experience
Manage our relationship with you
Provide social features as part of the Service
Customize your Service experience
Respond to your comments and questions and provide player support
Provide you Gogii offers in the Service as well as in other websites and services, and by email
Send you related information, such as updates, security alerts, and support messages
Enable you to communicate with other players
To detect and prevent illegal activities (e.g. hacking or cheating)
To conduct research
To analyze, profile, and segment.
In all of the above cases and purposes, we may analyze, profile and segment all collected data.
3.3 TO SHOW PERSONALIZED ADVERTISEMENTS.
To show you personalized advertisements in the Service as well as in other websites and services (including email) we have a legitimate interest to process necessary data to
Track the content you access in connection with the Service and your online behavior
Deliver, target and improve our advertising and the Service
3.4 WITH YOUR CONSENT
With your consent, we may process your data for additional purposes, such as using your GPS location to show you local events.
4. WE ALSO SHARE DATA WITH KEY PARTNERS
4.1 WHAT DATA WE MIGHT SHARE
Data we receive if you link a third party tool with the Service (Facebook,)
Demographic data (such as to determine the coarse location of your IP address)
Data to fight fraud (such as refund abuse in games or click fraud in advertising)
Data from platforms that the games run on (such as to verify payment)
Data for advertising and analytics purposes, so we can provide you a better Service
4.2 WHO DO WE SHARE YOUR DATA WITH
* Other players in order to provide certain in-app features, such as leaderboards, if you log into the App using a third-party service, such as Facebook or Apple or Game Center.
* Advertising network companies in order to serve contextual advertisements (the data include your IP-address, Device ID and advertising ID).
