5. HOW WE PROTECT YOUR DATA
5.1 Security In order to help ensure a secure and safe player experience, we are continuously working with our partners to offer the most advance measures to protect your data.
5.2 Data Retention We retain your data for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you the Service.
6. COOKIES AND SIMILAR TECHNOLOGIES
We and our partners use cookies and similar technologies to provide and personalize the Service, analyse use, target advertisements and prevent fraud. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, but some parts of the Service may then not function properly.
7 AGE LIMITS
We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal data about or direct or target interest based advertising to anyone under the age of 13 or knowingly allow such persons to use our Services. If you are under 13, please do not send any data about yourself to us, including your name, address, telephone number, or email address. No one under the age of 13 may provide any personal data. If we learn that we have collected personal data about a child under age 13, we will delete that data as quickly as possible. If you believe that we might have any data from or about a child under the age of 13, please contact us.
8. YOUR RIGHTS AND OPTIONS
8.1 Opt-out of marketing emails and other direct marketing.
You may opt-out of receiving promotional communications, such as marketing emails from us by following the instructions in such communications.
8.2 Opt-out of targeted advertising.
You can opt-out of interest-based advertising on mobile applications by checking the privacy settings of your Android or iOS device and selecting "limit ad tracking" (Apple iOS) or "opt-out of interest based ads" (Android). For more information, see also:
Faccebook Privacy Policy: https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy
Google Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
Twitter Privacy Policy: https://twitter.com/en/privacy
Unity Technologies Privacy Policy: https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
For personalized in-game offers opt-out, you can use the options provided in the game settings.
8.3 Access the personal data we hold about you.
If you request, we will provide you with a copy of your personal data in an electronic format.
8.4 Your other rights.
You can always withdraw your consent, for example, by turning off GPS location sharing in your mobile device settings.
Depending upon the applicable law where you live, you may have the right to make requests with respect to personal data that Gogii Games processes about you, for example, to request:
·      information
·      access
·      correction (or rectification) of personal data that you think is incorrect
·      Deletion
·      an electronic copy
·      You may also have the right to object to certain processing, including to opt out of targeted advertising.
To access your data in our games or to request its deletion, please use the in-game contact support feature provided in our games. You will find them in the game settings screen. Select the contact support button to launch an email with your game’s vital information. Please indicate your privacy policy request inside the support email. Alternatively, you can contact Gogii Games by sending an email to
privacy@gogiigames.com
. To fulfill requests submitted by email, we may need to confirm your identity to verify your right to make the request, which may involve requesting additional information from you. While we will usually not do so, we reserve the right to charge you an appropriate fee for the exercise of your rights where permitted by applicable laws and regulations.